      "demo_behavior": "Module: TopModule I would like you to implement a module named TopModule with the following interface. All input and output ports are one bit unless otherwise specified. - input  a (5 bits) - input  b (5 bits) - input  c (5 bits) - input  d (5 bits) - input  e (5 bits) - input  f (5 bits) - output w (8 bits) - output x (8 bits) - output y (8 bits) - output z (8 bits) The module should concatenate the input vectors together then split them up into several output vectors. There are six 5-bit input vectors: a, b, c, d, e, and f, for a total of 30 bits of input. There are four 8-bit output vectors: w, x, y, and z, for 32 bits of output. The output should be a concatenation of the input vectors followed by two 1 bits (the two 1 bits should be in the LSB positions).\nKey rules: Implement behavior exactly as described in the prompt.\nReset: Only as explicitly described in the prompt.\nCorner cases: No additional corner cases beyond prompt requirements.\nPerformance: Use prompt-defined timing/latency behavior.",
